Doesn't seem horrible:

```
{
  "kind": "pod",
  "status": {
    "status": "waiting",
    "hostIP": "172.34.56.1"
  }
}
```

What about:
    { "spec": { ... }, "current": { "status":"waiting" } }  # type Pod { PodSpec, PodReport { PodStatus }}
or
    { "spec": { ... }, "status": { "state":"waiting" } }  # yes, we just undid this
or
    { "spec": { ... }, "status": { "condition":"waiting" } } # type Pod { PodSpec, PodStatus { PodCondition }}
or 
    { "spec": { ... }, "status": { "currently":"waiting" } } # type Pod { PodSpec, PodStatus { PodStatusCode }}

Those are my final words on this.  I will not bikeshed further execpt to say that "Status" is OK as a group of data points, "State" is not.  IMO.  Please choose one of the above, a combination of the above, or something you like better.

